typedef void(* CodecDevice::CbResult)(ResultType result, void *context)
 

Callback function that is invoked by the CodecDevice when the corresponding asynchronous operation has been finished.

Parameters:
result A result (error) code: Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.
context A context (e.g. this pointer) that has been passed to the CodecDevice object when the corresponding function has been invoked.
See also:
CbResultAndTimeInfo

typedef void(* CodecDevice::CbResultAndTimeInfo)(ResultType result, void *context, UINT32 time_ms)
 

Callback function that is invoked by the CodecDevice when the corresponding asynchronous operation has been finished. In addition, the current clock time is provided (if suppoted).

Parameters:
result A result (error) code: Success if the operation was successful. Otherwise, an appropriate error code.
context A context (e.g. this pointer) that has been passed to the CodecDevice object when the corresponding function has been invoked.
time_ms Current clock time (in milliseconds). If CodecDevice object does not support time, this value has to be ignored.
See also:
CbResult

enum CodecDevice::CodecType
 

Codec.

Enumerator:
DefaultCodec  CodecManager should select a suitable/default codec. It is used for encoding purposes.
UnknownCodec  Codec is unknown to the encoder/decoder, i.e., the codec is not supported by the encoder/decoder.
Mpeg4Sp  MPEG-4 Simple Profile.
H263Bl  H.263 Baseline.
GsmAmrNb  GSM AMR Narrow Band.
Mpeg4Aac  AAC-LC (or AAC-LTP).
Qcelp  QCELP.
Evrc  EVRC.
Mp3  MP3.
Mpeg4AacPlusV1  AAC-Plus V1 (= AAC+ = HE-AAC = AAC-LC + SBR).
Mpeg4AacPlusV2  AAC-Plus V2 (= AAC++ = Enhanced AAC+ = AAC-LC + SBR + PS).
H264Bp  H.264 Baseline Profile.
EndOfCodecType

enum CodecDevice::ResultType
 

Result (error) codes that are usually returned by the functions of the CodecManager, VideoEncoder, VideoDecoder and AudioDecoder.

Enumerator:
Success  Function successfully completed.
MediaNotSupported  MIME type or codec is not supported.
OutOfMemory 
SmallBuffer  Buffer length (size) is too short.
NullParameter 
InvalidParameter 
InvalidFrameSize 
FeatureNotSupported  The feature is not supported (e.g. due to HW constraints).
GeneralError  General or unknown error.
MaxNumberOfCodersReached  The maximum number of Encoders/Decoders has been already created.
MaxNumberOfOperationsReached  The maximum number of invocations of this function has been reached, i.e., the queue is full.
ArrayTooShort  Insufficient number of elements in the array.
InvalidState
